The catch: the model file is 8.3 MB. First load takes about 1.2 seconds on a fast connection. Inference takes roughly 180-220 milliseconds per image. You're also pulling in onnxruntime-web which adds about 2 MB to your bundle.

But the output is dramatically better. Hair strands, fur, transparent objects — things the Canvas approach can't touch — get handled reasonably well.

